  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Maryland for FY2026 to date total $22.5B across 63,329 awards, with an average award size of $355K. Totals are fiscal year to date and therefore partial. Obligations are down 43.4% year over year. Annual obligations in prior full fiscal years ranged from $39.2B in FY21 to $46.3B in FY24 and $39.7B in FY25; FY26 to date is $22.5B. The Department of Defense is the largest buyer in FY2026 to date at $8.7B, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $4.4B and the Department of Energy at $1.9B. Leading vendors in FY2026 to date include THE JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY APPLIED PHYSICS LABORATORY LLC at $1.2B, ORANO FEDERAL SERVICES LLC at $900M, and AMERICAN CENTRIFUGE OPERATING, LLC at $900M. Top industry categories by obligations in FY2026 to date include Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $2.4B and Computer Systems Design Services at $2.3B. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies account for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense leads FY2026 to date obligations at $8.7B, followed by the Department of Health and Human Services at $4.4B and the Department of Energy at $1.9B. Smaller but notable buyers include the Department of Homeland Security at $1.3B and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration at $1.2B. Together these agencies represent the largest concentrated sources of federal contract obligations in Maryland for the fiscal year to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the top vendors and which industries receive the most obligations?",
        "body": "THE JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY APPLIED PHYSICS LABORATORY LLC is the top vendor in FY2026 to date at $1.2B, with ORANO FEDERAL SERVICES LLC and AMERICAN CENTRIFUGE OPERATING, LLC each at $900M. Leading industry categories by obligations in FY2026 to date include Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $2.4B, Computer Systems Design Services at $2.3B, and Engineering Services at $2.3B. These vendors and industries reflect the state’s concentration in defense, R&D, and advanced engineering services."
      }
    ]
  },
